                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d131">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Conger</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-01-07">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 7, 1902</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Conger reports that a memorandum has been left with him by the Russian
                    minister reporting three attacks by American sailors on Russian soldiers at
                    Niuchwang, one of the latter being wounded, and <pb facs="0226" n="146"
                        xml:id="pg_146"/> reporting Admiral Alleexieff as saying that he fears a
                    continuance of such conduct will compel him to take severe measures to protect
                    his soldiers, and that henceforth he will disclaim all responsibility for
                    resultant consequences; that relations between Russian and other officials there
                    are much strained; and suggesting that the commander of the <hi rend="italic"
                        >Vicksburg</hi> be instructed to use extra efforts to restrain his men.)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
